    Hanson Cement is known for regularly seeking and acting on customer feedback in the UK through its six-monthly customer satisfaction surveys with
    MRA Research. Hanson uses this feedback to measure satisfaction levels, identify potential issues, and inform its business strategy for improving its products and services. 
    • Regular Feedback: Hanson conducts customer surveys every six months to track satisfaction trends over time and to address any immediate issues.
    • Strategic Improvement: The company uses the results and recommendations to shape its future strategy, improve overall service levels, and develop products that add value for its customers.
    • Demonstrated Improvement: The surveys have shown marked improvements in overall satisfaction and a significant increase in its Net Promoter Score (NPS).

    What are the cement companies in the UK?
    An AI Overview is not available for this searchCan't generate an AI overview right now. Try again later.
    AI Overview
    Major cement companies in the UK include Cemex UK, Tarmac (Blue Circle), Hanson Cement, and Breedon Cement, which are among the dominant players in the industry. Other companies like Heidelberg Materials UK also manufacture and supply cement and related products.
     
    Major UK cement companies
    • Cemex UK:
      Supplies bagged and bulk cement and operates a network of plants across the country. 
    • Tarmac:
      The company's Blue Circle brand is a leading cement brand in the UK, providing products for various applications from infrastructure projects to DIY. 
    • Hanson Cement:
      Offers a wide range of cement products, including Portland Cement and White Portland Cement, along with GGBS and Fly Ash. 
    • Breedon Cement:
      A key producer of cement and other construction materials in Great Britain and Ireland, with its Hope Cement Plant in Derbyshire being the UK's largest. 
    • Heidelberg Materials UK:
      Produces cement in bulk and bags, along with low-carbon alternatives like GGBS and captured carbon cement. 
    Other companies
    • Aggregate Industries UK: One of the four large companies that dominate the industry, as noted by IBISWorld. 
    • SpecifiedBy: Lists over 10 manufacturers, including Fermacell, Mapei UK, and Bostik, alongside the major players. 
    • Ecocem: Also listed by SpecifiedBy as a UK cement manufacturer.

      Foreword

      The primary mission of this Government and the driving force of the Department for Business and Trade (DBT) is stronger economic growth: not just growth that looks good on paper, but growth that is seen and is felt on our high streets, in our towns and cities, and in the communities we serve. Good regulation, delivered in the right way, supports innovation and growth. In March this year the government published its action plan to ensure that regulation and regulators support economic growth.

      The Office for Product Safety and Standards (OPSS) is the UK's national product regulator and sits at the heart of our product regulation system. Its primary purpose is to protect people and places from product-related harm, enabling trade and growth by ensuring consumers and businesses can buy and sell products with confidence. An effective product regulatory system ensures shops and small businesses can compete on a level playing field with online marketplaces and global tech companies, and...  More

      Executive summary

      OPSS is the UK's national product regulator. The regulations we enforce ensure that everyday products such as toys, electricals and cosmetics are safe for use; they ensure accurate weighing and measuring so that consumers get what they pay for; they ensure construction products perform as they should in the built environment; and they ensure products such as timber and electricals are sourced or disposed of in the right way to avoid harm to the environment.

      We support DBT ministers in the development and implementation of product safety, metrology and hallmarking policy, and MHCLG Ministers on associated responsibilities relating to construction products. We enforce product regulations for six different government departments, sometimes acting as the sole enforcement authority and in other areas working with local authorities to coordinate national and local enforcement activities.
